Dr Tumi Picture: supplied
Award-winning musician Dr Tumi may be one of the biggest gospel artists in the country‚ but he says the genre has some way to go in matching the originality found in other music.
He told Power FM’s Tumelo Mothotoane that he dreamed of a day where he could walk into a music store and every gospel album was unique.
“South African gospel music has come a long way‚ but one of things that is my personal dream is when you can go into a store to buy music,” Dr Tumi said.


“When you can go to the gospel music shelf and every album you pick up is new content‚ not recycled.
“I believe there is still a lot of recycling that happens.”
Dr Tumi has transformed the gospel industry‚ releasing fresh music and recently filling the Ticketpro Dome in Johannesburg – a first for a gospel artist.


